1
00:00:11,583 --> 00:00:13,000
I'd like to thank everyone
for gathering here.

2
00:00:13,083 --> 00:00:15,250
All we had to do
was come downstairs.

3
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:17,750
I kinda figured that
you would've given up by now.

4
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,291
Like I told you already,

5
00:00:19,375 --> 00:00:21,166
we don't need
some know-it-all to tutor us.

6
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:23,458
If you're so smart,
then prove it to me.

7
00:00:24,875 --> 00:00:27,833
-Prove it to you?
-[FUTARO] Shouldn't be hard.

8
00:00:27,916 --> 00:00:29,458
You just have to take this test!

9
00:00:30,791 --> 00:00:32,875
Here's your golden opportunity.

10
00:00:32,958 --> 00:00:35,375
Pass the test, and I swear
I'll never speak to you again.

11
00:00:35,458 --> 00:00:37,083
[ALL gasp]

12
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,541
What? Is he serious?

13
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:41,083
What test?

14
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:44,291
I don't even care, so why would
I take your dumb test?

15
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:46,416
All right, fine. I'll take it.

16
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,041
[NINO]
You can't be serious.

17
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:52,583
I just need to get
a passing grade.

18
00:00:54,291 --> 00:00:57,208
And then I'll never have
to see your face again.

19
00:00:57,291 --> 00:01:00,291
Aww, yeah! Let's do it!

20
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:02,625
Sounds pretty easy.

21
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:04,833
Define "passing grade."

22
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:06,666
Sixty-- no, wait.

23
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:09,000
I'd say a score of fifty
is adequate.

24
00:01:09,083 --> 00:01:10,416
[sighs]

25
00:01:10,500 --> 00:01:11,791
[NINO]
There's no reason we should have

26
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:13,791
to prove ourselves to you,

27
00:01:13,875 --> 00:01:16,958
but it's time you learned
not to underestimate us.

28
00:01:17,041 --> 00:01:21,458
[clock ticking]

29
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:30,333
[FUTARO]
Finished grading your tests!

30
00:01:30,416 --> 00:01:33,666
Wow, you all scored
a hundred points!

31
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:34,750
[groans]

32
00:01:35,916 --> 00:01:39,125
-Combined, that is.
-[YOTSUBA chuckles awkwardly]

33
00:01:39,208 --> 00:01:40,791
[FUTARO]
This is abysmal.

34
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:44,583
[NINO] Run for it!
[panting]

35
00:01:44,666 --> 00:01:45,875
[YOTSUBA giggles]

36
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:49,458
This is worse than I thought.

37
00:01:49,541 --> 00:01:52,625
All five of these girls
could flunk out!

38
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:26,458
[panting]

39
00:03:26,541 --> 00:03:27,583
Damn it.

40
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:30,541
I had no idea...

41
00:03:31,875 --> 00:03:34,291
tutoring and doing
my own homework...

42
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:38,333
would be this difficult.

43
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:41,583
-Barely made it.
-[tires screeching]

44
00:03:43,541 --> 00:03:44,791
What the...

45
00:03:44,875 --> 00:03:46,916
That's one swanky limo.

46
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,541
Bet this is worth
at least a million.

47
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:55,333
Um, hi? What's your deal?

48
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,666
Stop staring and move aside.

49
00:03:57,750 --> 00:04:00,041
-[YOTSUBA] Good morning, Futaro!
-You again?

50
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:01,750
-[ICHIKA] Oh hey, Futaro!
-[MIKU] Mmm.

51
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:07,125
Stop running! Get back here!

52
00:04:07,208 --> 00:04:08,250
Hey, check it out!

53
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:11,750
I'm book free now!
Perfectly safe!

54
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:14,583
-We're not falling for that!
-Don't trust him.

55
00:04:14,666 --> 00:04:17,125
He'll find a way
to teach us something.

56
00:04:17,208 --> 00:04:19,625
Just what kind of person
do you think I am?

57
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:22,541
[ITSUKI] I'll admit that
each of us has shortcomings.

58
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:26,041
But we can manage just fine
without any help from you.

59
00:04:26,125 --> 00:04:28,750
We don't need a chaperone
while we study.

60
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,250
What she said.

61
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:31,875
[FUTARO]
I see.

62
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:34,625
Then I can assume you reviewed
the test by yourselves.

63
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:36,500
[ALL chuckle awkwardly]

64
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:39,083
Question one:

65
00:04:39,166 --> 00:04:41,416
Name the warlord
defeated by Mori Motonari

66
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:43,166
at the Battle of Itsukushima.

67
00:04:46,708 --> 00:04:48,208
[ITSUKI chuckles]

68
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:54,541
No answer?

69
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:56,500
-It's no mystery.
-[GIRLS chattering]

70
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:59,958
[FUTARO]
These five girls abhor studying.

71
00:05:00,041 --> 00:05:03,875
But... it seems they hate me
just as much.

72
00:05:05,958 --> 00:05:09,208
I need to find a way to earn
their trust individually.

73
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:11,125
Huh? Wait a minute.

74
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:14,166
Miku answered
that question right.

75
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,958
So then, why...

76
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:24,125
Miku?

77
00:05:24,208 --> 00:05:27,625
[STUDENTS chattering]

78
00:05:27,708 --> 00:05:30,041
[WOMAN] One barbecue beef combo,
hold the-- Uh!

79
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,916
-[FUTARO] Hey, Miku.
-Hmm?

80
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,208
[chuckles awkwardly]

81
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:38,916
What you eatin' for lunch?

82
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,291
Um, let's see here,
you have a sandwich

83
00:05:41,375 --> 00:05:44,375
for 350 yen, and, uh...

84
00:05:44,458 --> 00:05:46,333
What kind of drink is that?

85
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:48,000
[MIKU]
Matcha Soda.

86
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:50,750
[FUTARO] Matcha?
Hmm, interesting.

87
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:52,666
I'm curious what
that flavor tastes like.

88
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,916
Well, I would let you
try some of mine,

89
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,500
but you're a mean person.

90
00:05:57,583 --> 00:06:00,208
Can I at least
ask you something?

91
00:06:00,291 --> 00:06:01,916
About that test question...

92
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:06,625
[YOTSUBA]
Hey, Mr. Tutor!

93
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:08,166
Ah! Yotsuba!

94
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,916
Sorry we all ran away
this morning.

95
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,291
It's nothing personal!

96
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:12,625
Eh, so, Miku--

97
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:14,916
Get a load of this!
My English homework!

98
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,083
I got every
single question wrong!

99
00:06:19,166 --> 00:06:21,666
Come on. Let's give 'em
some privacy.

100
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,166
How come?

101
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:25,291
I was just gonna
ask him to help me.

102
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,333
You should, too.

103
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:29,208
Yeah.
That's a hard pass.

104
00:06:29,291 --> 00:06:31,333
I mean, why bother?
We're all dumb.

105
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:33,500
[FUTARO]
All the more reason to study.

106
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:35,000
Studying sucks!

107
00:06:35,083 --> 00:06:36,833
Do you really want to waste
your high school years

108
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:38,875
with your nose
stuck in a book?

109
00:06:38,958 --> 00:06:41,750
We should be out there
enjoying our youth!

110
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:43,333
Falling in love!

111
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,666
[FUTARO]
Love.

112
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,333
There's no bigger waste of time

113
00:06:48,416 --> 00:06:51,708
than ignoring scholastic
endeavors for romance.

114
00:06:51,791 --> 00:06:53,833
Go ahead and fall in love
if you want.

115
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:55,666
You'll end up like
all the other fools in the world

116
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:56,916
who peak in high school

117
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,333
and do nothing else
with their lives.

118
00:06:58,416 --> 00:07:00,750
That really struck a chord.
What's that about?

119
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:05,000
I'm not into anyone right now,
even if I wanted to date.

120
00:07:05,083 --> 00:07:08,458
What about you, Miku?
Do you have a crush on anyone?

121
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,583
Ew. No way.

122
00:07:13,791 --> 00:07:15,708
That was a weird reaction.

123
00:07:15,791 --> 00:07:17,375
The look on her face.

124
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:19,791
As her sister, I know
what that look means!

125
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:21,041
No freaking way!

126
00:07:21,125 --> 00:07:22,875
[BOTH together]
Miku is in love!

127
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:24,375
[FUTARO]
Huh?

128
00:07:24,458 --> 00:07:26,125
Miku is in love?

129
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:31,583
I need to get these girls
studying one way or another.

130
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:32,625
Huh?

131
00:07:32,708 --> 00:07:35,666
What the...
From Miku?

132
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:41,333
[MIKU] "Come to the rooftop
after school.

133
00:07:41,416 --> 00:07:43,958
"There's something
I want to tell you.

134
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:46,458
I just can't hold it in
any longer."

135
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:50,625
[FUTARO]
Hold on!

136
00:07:50,708 --> 00:07:54,000
A love letter?
Miku's in love with me?

137
00:07:54,083 --> 00:07:56,125
But we just met three days ago!

138
00:07:57,916 --> 00:07:59,750
Okay, what's that look
on your face about?

139
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:01,625
I swear, you're so creepy.

140
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:04,375
Hey! I am not creepy!

141
00:08:05,416 --> 00:08:09,125
Miku's pranking me.
Be cool, you got this.

142
00:08:09,208 --> 00:08:11,000
You don't need to put up
with this nonsense,

143
00:08:11,083 --> 00:08:12,750
and you don't need
to go to the roof.

144
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,250
Nuh-uh!

145
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:17,583
You see?

146
00:08:18,708 --> 00:08:21,500
I knew it was a juvenile prank
from the very beginning.

147
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:24,916
It's not like I secretly hoped
that she'd...

148
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,375
-[door opens]
-[gasps]

149
00:08:27,875 --> 00:08:28,833
[squeaky voice]
...show up!

150
00:08:28,916 --> 00:08:30,166
Thank goodness.

151
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:32,833
Hi. I'm glad you came.

152
00:08:34,750 --> 00:08:37,208
I actually wanted to tell you
back in the cafeteria.

153
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:40,833
But I didn't want to risk
anybody hearing me.

154
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:42,333
[FUTARO]
What?

155
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:44,583
I don't like
where this is going.

156
00:08:44,666 --> 00:08:48,041
Futaro. It's just...

157
00:08:48,125 --> 00:08:50,541
[BOTH together]
Miku is in love!

158
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:53,375
[FUTARO]
Um, yeah?

159
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:56,166
[MIKU]
There's something...

160
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:58,250
-I need to tell you.
-[wind gusting]

161
00:08:58,333 --> 00:08:59,375
I...

162
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:02,541
[FUTARO]
You?

163
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:03,750
[MIKU]
...I knew.

164
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:12,000
It was Sue Harukata.

165
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,166
Sue Harukata?

166
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,750
Right! I did it.
I'm good now.

167
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:25,291
Whoa! Timeout here!
You did what?

168
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:27,083
I don't understand
what you're trying to say.

169
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:30,416
The correct answer.
You don't remember it?

170
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:31,583
Your question.

171
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:32,916
My question?

172
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,625
Uh! That one?

173
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:37,125
Hey! Wait!

174
00:09:37,208 --> 00:09:39,125
Why did you go through
so much trouble

175
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:40,958
to tell me that in private?

176
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:44,083
[MIKU gasps]

177
00:09:45,375 --> 00:09:47,375
Ahh! I'm sorry!

178
00:09:50,708 --> 00:09:52,583
Is that the Takeda crest?

179
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:55,791
Isn't that Takeda Shingen's?

180
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:58,375
You saw it?

181
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:00,750
Huh? Wha...

182
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:03,875
Uh. Yeah?
[whimpers]

183
00:10:05,666 --> 00:10:07,250
-[MIKU cries]
-Huh?

184
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,666
Please.

185
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:10,291
Don't tell anyone

186
00:10:10,375 --> 00:10:13,958
that I like
Sengoku period warlords.

187
00:10:14,041 --> 00:10:15,291
Huh?

188
00:10:15,375 --> 00:10:16,625
[MIKU]
It all started with a game

189
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:17,958
I borrowed from Yotsuba.

190
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:22,083
I became obsessed
with the ambitious warlords

191
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:24,416
and read a lot of books, too.

192
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:27,375
But the girls at school
are only into good-looking guys.

193
00:10:27,458 --> 00:10:30,291
Actors, models,
you know, that type.

194
00:10:30,375 --> 00:10:34,250
And I like hairy old men.
I'm weird.

195
00:10:34,333 --> 00:10:36,541
[FUTARO]
Yeah, I can't unpack that.

196
00:10:36,625 --> 00:10:38,708
But I'm not writing her off
as a student.

197
00:10:38,791 --> 00:10:41,083
No way! There's still a chance.

198
00:10:41,166 --> 00:10:43,833
♪

199
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:45,291
You're not weird.

200
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:47,625
You should be confident
about the things you like.

201
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:51,625
And, as it happens,
my last history test,

202
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:52,916
I landed a perfect score.

203
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:54,416
Wow, really?

204
00:10:55,416 --> 00:10:57,791
Expect no less
from the top of the class!

205
00:10:58,916 --> 00:11:00,458
Allow me to tutor you,

206
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:03,250
and I'll teach you things
about warlords you never knew!

207
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:06,875
Not a chance.

208
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:09,125
You think you know more
about them than I do?

209
00:11:10,291 --> 00:11:12,375
All right, let's see
how you do on a pop quiz:

210
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:13,708
It's a commonly told story that

211
00:11:13,791 --> 00:11:15,625
Nobunaga used to call
Hideyoshi a monkey,

212
00:11:15,708 --> 00:11:17,458
but historians say
this is a false claim.

213
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:19,333
What was his actual nickname?

214
00:11:20,416 --> 00:11:21,625
[FUTARO]
Whoa, that's a lot!

215
00:11:21,708 --> 00:11:25,041
Okay, think.
What's Hideyoshi's nickname?

216
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:27,625
I'm pretty sure
my history teacher covered this.

217
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:31,833
♪

218
00:11:31,916 --> 00:11:34,541
Was it "bald rat"?

219
00:11:34,625 --> 00:11:35,833
That's correct.

220
00:11:35,916 --> 00:11:38,250
I owe you one, Teach!

221
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,583
Do you know
about the theory that

222
00:11:39,666 --> 00:11:41,208
Kenshin was actually a woman?

223
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:43,583
[FUTARO]
Yeah, totally. Old news.

224
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:46,666
And Mitsunari,
he didn't eat the persimmons.

225
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:48,166
[FUTARO]
Nope, not a bite.

226
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,583
Nobunaga served sake
in the skulls

227
00:11:51,666 --> 00:11:52,916
of his vanquished enemies.

228
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:56,458
Uh, yeah. He sure did.
[chuckles]

229
00:11:57,541 --> 00:11:59,000
I get it.

230
00:11:59,083 --> 00:12:01,750
Warlords are the one thing
linking Miku and history.

231
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:05,041
She might not like studying,
but I can use this.

232
00:12:05,125 --> 00:12:06,166
It's my way in!

233
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,458
Another one?

234
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:10,750
Nah. I should be
heading home, actually.

235
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:13,583
But I do want to talk
about this some more.

236
00:12:13,666 --> 00:12:15,125
Shoot.

237
00:12:15,208 --> 00:12:18,041
And I have so many stories
I bet you've never heard.

238
00:12:19,208 --> 00:12:20,333
I know!

239
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,541
Let's make Japanese history
the focus

240
00:12:23,625 --> 00:12:25,291
of our next tutoring session.

241
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:27,333
How's that?
Are you interested?

242
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:36,166
I mean, if you insist...

243
00:12:37,166 --> 00:12:38,291
then okay.

244
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:42,000
[FUTARO]
Victory!

245
00:12:43,375 --> 00:12:45,583
I need to locate
a decent study area.

246
00:12:45,666 --> 00:12:47,583
The rest should be no problem.

247
00:12:47,666 --> 00:12:49,666
My livelihood depends
on these girls.

248
00:12:49,750 --> 00:12:51,500
-[vending machine rattles]
-I need to stay focused.

249
00:12:51,583 --> 00:12:53,041
-[MIKU] Wait up.
-Yeah?

250
00:12:54,041 --> 00:12:56,541
For you.
As a token of good will.

251
00:12:57,708 --> 00:12:58,875
Here, try it.

252
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:04,041
You wanted to taste it earlier.
But don't worry.

253
00:13:05,583 --> 00:13:07,875
This doesn't have
any of my snot in it.

254
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:10,208
No need to be scared.

255
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,583
[FUTARO]
Hold on,

256
00:13:12,666 --> 00:13:14,666
did she really
just say, "snot"?

257
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:15,875
What's she talking about?

258
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:21,291
What's this? I stumped you?

259
00:13:21,375 --> 00:13:23,333
You don't know about that one?

260
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:26,500
Bummer.

261
00:13:29,416 --> 00:13:31,833
I thought you were
Mister "Top of the Class."

262
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:33,500
Turns out you're all talk.

263
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:36,916
I have nothing
to learn from you.

264
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,125
Farewell.

265
00:13:39,875 --> 00:13:41,708
-[FUTARO grunts]
-[WOMAN screams]

266
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:43,833
[FUTARO]
I'm checking out these books.

267
00:13:43,916 --> 00:13:45,791
Okay, sure.

268
00:13:45,875 --> 00:13:49,166
[FUTARO] "All talk," am I?
How dare she?

269
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:53,000
I'm gonna tutor that smug brat
whether she likes it or not!

270
00:13:53,083 --> 00:13:56,041
[horn blowing]

271
00:13:57,583 --> 00:14:00,291
Miku! At long last,
you have arrived.

272
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,625
What do you want now, Futaro?

273
00:14:04,708 --> 00:14:06,875
Use your wits to fight me!

274
00:14:06,958 --> 00:14:08,541
Come again?

275
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:10,625
You're a Sengoku
trivia master, right?

276
00:14:10,708 --> 00:14:13,666
Quiz me and I won't miss
a single question.

277
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,333
Not interested.
I'll just embarrass you.

278
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:19,833
Ha! Are you afraid I'll beat you
at your only skill?

279
00:14:19,916 --> 00:14:21,250
[MIKU growls]

280
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:25,375
In Takeda Shingen's
"Furinkazan,"

281
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:27,250
which phrase refers to "wind."

282
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:31,416
I thought you'd
give me a hard one.

283
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:35,583
The answer is.
"As swift as the wind."

284
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:37,833
♪

285
00:14:37,916 --> 00:14:39,750
Come on!

286
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,833
She's high-tailing it again?

287
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:45,250
You know what? I'm getting tired
of chasing after these girls!

288
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,750
They run from me,
they run from studying.

289
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:50,166
But she's not getting away!

290
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:54,500
♪

291
00:14:54,583 --> 00:14:56,375
Whoa! Uesugi!

292
00:14:56,458 --> 00:14:58,291
Uh, Yotsuba?

293
00:14:58,375 --> 00:14:59,708
You should watch
where you're going

294
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:01,083
if you're gonna run around.

295
00:15:01,166 --> 00:15:03,166
Do you know
if Miku came this way?

296
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:05,708
Yeah, I think I saw her
heading in that direction.

297
00:15:05,791 --> 00:15:07,125
Thanks.

298
00:15:07,208 --> 00:15:08,750
Man, where could she have gone?

299
00:15:10,416 --> 00:15:12,416
Whoa! Uesugi!

300
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:13,833
[FUTARO]
Wait, how'd you get there?

301
00:15:13,916 --> 00:15:15,125
You should watch
where you're going

302
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:16,375
if you're gonna run around.

303
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:18,708
[GIRLS] Left! Right! Left!
Right! Left!

304
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:20,041
What's wrong?

305
00:15:20,125 --> 00:15:22,583
Sorry, Yotsuba.
Keep calm and listen close.

306
00:15:22,666 --> 00:15:25,708
Your doppelganger
is standing over there.

307
00:15:25,791 --> 00:15:27,791
[YOTSUBA] For real?
[gasps]

308
00:15:27,875 --> 00:15:29,458
It's totally me!

309
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:31,166
That means you're dead.

310
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:33,958
Huh?
I don't wanna die!

311
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:37,958
Wow. I wonder what I should have
for my last meal?

312
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:41,000
Hey, is it just me,
or does she have longer hair?

313
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:44,375
And she took off her ribbon.

314
00:15:44,458 --> 00:15:46,500
Where'd those headphones
come from?

315
00:15:46,583 --> 00:15:49,250
-Hey, that's Miku!
-Oh, thank goodness!

316
00:15:50,875 --> 00:15:53,208
[FUTARO] Think you can pull
a fast one on me, huh?

317
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:54,958
I'm sorry for lying
to you the other day!

318
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:57,041
I spent the past two days

319
00:15:57,125 --> 00:15:59,458
reading every single book
in the library

320
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:02,125
about the Sengoku period!

321
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:04,583
That is such a lie!

322
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:08,125
[BOTH panting]

323
00:16:08,208 --> 00:16:10,000
-I know, right?
-[laughing]

324
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:11,750
Uh, hmm?

325
00:16:11,833 --> 00:16:13,000
-What the...
-Huh?

326
00:16:14,041 --> 00:16:16,333
[FUTARO]
I put in the work studying!

327
00:16:16,416 --> 00:16:18,833
I can talk to you
as an equal now!

328
00:16:18,916 --> 00:16:22,375
[panting]

329
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:25,666
[MIKU]
Warlord shiritori.

330
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:28,541
Ryuzoji Takanobu.

331
00:16:28,625 --> 00:16:31,916
Huh? [panting]

332
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,958
Oh! I know this game!

333
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:36,416
Fukushima Masanori.

334
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,083
From the battle in 1583,

335
00:16:38,166 --> 00:16:41,375
he was the most prominent of
the Seven Spears of Shizugatake!

336
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:44,750
Kanamori Nagachika.

337
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,541
[MIKU]
Ka... Kawajiri Hidetaka.

338
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:50,375
Katakura Kojuro.

339
00:16:50,458 --> 00:16:52,916
Uesugi Kagekatsu.

340
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,666
[FUTARO]
Tsu... Tsuda Nobuzumi.

341
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:59,083
Mi... Miyoshi Nagayoshi.

342
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:03,666
Shi... Shi... Shimazu Toyohisa.

343
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:06,833
Sa... Sanada Yukimura.

344
00:17:06,916 --> 00:17:10,833
-I can't keep going.
-Ra... Ahh!

345
00:17:10,916 --> 00:17:15,666
Why... are you trying...
so hard?

346
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,208
[bodies thud]

347
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:21,500
[BOTH panting]

348
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:23,291
[FUTARO]
You're pretty good at that.

349
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:27,208
I didn't think
you could keep up.

350
00:17:27,291 --> 00:17:30,083
Yeah, well, the truth is,

351
00:17:30,166 --> 00:17:32,250
I'm the slowest runner
in my class.

352
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,541
It's so hot.

353
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:46,291
Man. I need
a drink or something.

354
00:17:47,291 --> 00:17:48,708
No shame.

355
00:17:48,791 --> 00:17:51,208
She's just taking off
her clothes in public.

356
00:17:58,208 --> 00:17:59,458
-Here.
-Eee!

357
00:18:00,625 --> 00:18:04,583
Uh, sorry.
But you like this, don't you?

358
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:07,166
A hundred and ten yen
seems pretty steep to me,

359
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,208
but at least I know
there's no snot in it.

360
00:18:11,250 --> 00:18:12,916
Ishida Mitsunari, right?

361
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,833
I learned about the anecdote
where he drank tea

362
00:18:14,916 --> 00:18:16,583
with Otani Yoshitsugu's
snot in it.

363
00:18:16,666 --> 00:18:20,666
You have no idea how many books
I read searching for that story.

364
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,083
But I couldn't find it.

365
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:26,000
Lucky for me,
Yotsuba happened to be there,

366
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:27,750
and I looked it up
on her phone.

367
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:29,875
Yotsuba?

368
00:18:30,958 --> 00:18:32,958
Did you tell her
I like warlords?

369
00:18:33,041 --> 00:18:34,583
I asked you not to.

370
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,916
No, I didn't tell her.

371
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,208
Why would you keep something
like that from your sisters?

372
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:46,958
[MIKU] Because they
wouldn't understand.

373
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:48,083
[FUTARO]
Why not?

374
00:18:49,166 --> 00:18:50,791
They just wouldn't, okay?

375
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:53,583
I'm the biggest loser
of the five of us.

376
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:55,291
But you're actually doing
really well

377
00:18:55,375 --> 00:18:57,125
compared to the rest of them!

378
00:18:57,208 --> 00:18:59,500
You had the highest score
on that last exam.

379
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:02,875
You're just being nice.

380
00:19:02,958 --> 00:19:06,833
Well, you shouldn't exactly be
proud of the grades you did get.

381
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:08,375
[MIKU]
I know.

382
00:19:08,458 --> 00:19:10,416
We're not cut out for this.

383
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:13,041
My sisters can do
anything I can.

384
00:19:13,125 --> 00:19:16,833
So if this is my best,
then it's also their best.

385
00:19:16,916 --> 00:19:18,291
We are quintuplets!

386
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:21,375
[FUTARO]
Hang on.

387
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:24,416
If what Miku says is true,
then that means...

388
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:28,291
Just give up on me
and stop wasting your time.

389
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:30,833
[FUTARO] I was hired to tutor
all five of you.

390
00:19:31,916 --> 00:19:35,166
Listen to me.
I'm not giving up on any of you.

391
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,541
I will make sure
you all graduate together

392
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:39,916
with smiles on your faces!

393
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:42,916
[chuckles]

394
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:46,250
It's a nice thought,
but it won't happen.

395
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:47,666
We're failures.

396
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:50,250
It took all five of us
to score a hundred.

397
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:53,500
Yeah. You're a bunch
of failures, all right.

398
00:19:53,583 --> 00:19:56,166
Or so I believed, until today.

399
00:19:57,250 --> 00:19:58,750
Just now, you said something

400
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:00,208
that gave me hope
for all of you.

401
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:04,000
You're quintuplets.

402
00:20:04,083 --> 00:20:06,916
Your sisters can do anything
you can do, right?

403
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,458
Just flip that around.

404
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:09,958
Anything your sisters can do...

405
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:12,916
you can also do, Miku.

406
00:20:13,916 --> 00:20:15,500
Take a look at this.

407
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:16,958
These are the test results.

408
00:20:19,083 --> 00:20:21,083
See if you notice anything.

409
00:20:23,083 --> 00:20:24,750
[MIKU]
Our scores are different.

410
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:27,041
None of us got
the same answers right!

411
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:28,666
[FUTARO]
Exactly.

412
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:31,958
Your average is 20 points,
so we have a lot of work ahead.

413
00:20:32,041 --> 00:20:35,375
But I can see now
that you girls aren't hopeless.

414
00:20:35,458 --> 00:20:37,791
Whatever one of you can do,
all of you can do.

415
00:20:39,458 --> 00:20:41,083
Ichika...

416
00:20:41,166 --> 00:20:42,833
Nino...

417
00:20:42,916 --> 00:20:44,541
Yotsuba...

418
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:46,125
Itsuki.

419
00:20:48,291 --> 00:20:49,416
And you, Miku.

420
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:51,125
I believe in you!

421
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:52,750
Each one of you has
the potential

422
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:54,375
to score one hundred.

423
00:20:54,458 --> 00:20:55,708
All on your own!

424
00:20:56,750 --> 00:21:00,166
♪

425
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:02,125
[MIKU]
That's a stretch.

426
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:04,625
-Sorry, but...
-[pops can]

427
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:05,916
...it won't work.

428
00:21:10,125 --> 00:21:12,833
Don't put too much stock
in this quintuplets theory.

429
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:16,291
[FUTARO]
Ugh!

430
00:21:16,375 --> 00:21:18,625
I wish the other four came too.

431
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:19,916
[groans]

432
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,291
I called to let them know
where we were.

433
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:27,000
Hold up!
You better rethink that number.

434
00:21:30,625 --> 00:21:32,291
It's "the other three."

435
00:21:32,375 --> 00:21:33,958
Miku's here!

436
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:34,958
[FUTARO]
Hey!

437
00:21:35,041 --> 00:21:36,916
I'm so glad you decided to come!

438
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,625
We were just, uh...

439
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:52,583
[turning pages]

440
00:21:52,666 --> 00:21:54,041
[chuckles]

441
00:21:54,125 --> 00:21:56,666
[MIKU] Guess you could say
you got to me, Futaro.

442
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:58,166
I'm starting to think...

443
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:01,500
that maybe I can do
a little bit better, too.

444
00:22:03,541 --> 00:22:04,500
So...

445
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:08,208
♪

446
00:22:08,291 --> 00:22:09,416
...hope you're worth it.

447
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:10,958
I'm trusting you.

448
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:15,666
I'm your guy!

449
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:19,750
Miku, are you falling in love
with Uesugi or something?

450
00:22:21,541 --> 00:22:23,958
♪

451
00:22:27,541 --> 00:22:28,791
Ew, no way.

452
00:22:28,875 --> 00:22:30,000
[FUTARO]
Huh?

453
00:24:00,708 --> 00:24:02,625
[ALL]
Quintuplet Trivia!

454
00:24:02,708 --> 00:24:03,916
[YOTSUBA] Who do you think
has the best grades

455
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,541
of the five of us? Miku!

456
00:24:05,625 --> 00:24:07,083
[MIKU]
The brains of the quintuplets.

457
00:24:07,166 --> 00:24:08,875
-The strategist.
-[YOTSUBA] What's a strategist?

458
00:24:08,958 --> 00:24:10,666
[MIKU] A person who uses their
exceptional intellectual skills

459
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:13,291
to fine-tune and execute plans
of attack in Sengoku battles.

460
00:24:13,375 --> 00:24:14,916
[YOTSUBA]
That's too many words!

